Today's presidential speeches use simpler language than past ones
  
 Now, it's important to note that speeches using more complex words and language aren't necessarily better. Indeed, the whole point of this rating scale is that the higher your speech scores, the fewer people understand what you're talking about. Simplicity in language and word choice can often help a message be communicated effectively and powerfully, to an audience of people from many different backgrounds — and that's just what modern presidents and their speechwriters are trying to do.  Get our newsletter in your inbox twice a week. 